claim.claim-text:
A vane arm (140) comprising:
a first end (141) having a first surface (148) and a second surface (151) opposite the first surface (148); and
a vane stem aperture (146) formed through the first end (141) of the vane arm (140), wherein the first surface (148) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140) defines a first perimeter (160) of the vane stem aperture (146), and wherein the second surface (151) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140) defines a second perimeter (162) of the vane stem aperture (146), wherein the second perimeter (162) comprises a first shape that is at least one of circular or elliptical, and wherein the first perimeter (160) comprises a second shape different from the first shape;
characterised in that a radially inward portion (170) of the vane stem aperture (146) is defined, at least partially, by:
a first wedge face (174), a second wedge face (176), and a third wedge face (192), wherein the first wedge face (174), the second wedge face (176), and the third wedge face (192) each extends in a radially outward direction toward an axis (R-R') extending radially through a central point of the vane stem aperture (146); and
wherein a radially outward portion (172) of the vane stem aperture (146) is defined, at least partially, by:
a first vertical surface (182) extending between the first wedge face (174) and the first surface (148) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140);
a second vertical surface (184) extending between the second wedge face (176) and the first surface (148) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140);
a third vertical surface (194) extending between the third wedge face (192) and the first surface (148) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140); and
a fourth vertical surface (190b) located opposite the third vertical surface (194), wherein the first vertical surface (182), the second vertical surface (184), the third vertical surface (194), and the fourth vertical surface (190b) are each generally parallel to the axis (R-R') extending radially through the central point of the vane stem aperture (146); and
wherein the radially inward portion (170) of the vane stem aperture (146) is further defined, at least partially, by:
a further first vertical surface (178) extending between the first wedge face (174) and the second surface (151) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140);
a further second vertical surface (180) extending between the second wedge face (176) and the second surface (151) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140);
a further third vertical surface (196) extending between the third wedge face (192) and the second surface (151) of the first end (141) of the vane arm (140); and
a further fourth vertical surface (190a) located opposite the further third vertical surface (196), wherein the further first vertical surface (178), the further second vertical surface (180), the further third vertical surface (196), and the further fourth vertical surface (190a) are each generally parallel to the axis (R-R') extending radially through the central point of the vane stem aperture (146).
